  "prompt": "What are some good online interior design courses?",
  "response": "There are many great online interior design courses available, catering to various skill levels and interests. Here are some notable options to consider:\n\n1. **Coursera**:\n   - **Fundamentals of Graphic Design** by CalArts: While not exclusively about interior design, this course provides a solid foundation in design principles that can be applied to interiors.\n   - **Interior Design Courses**: Several universities offer specialized interior design courses and certificates.\n\n2. **Udemy**:\n   - **Interior Design 101**: A beginner-friendly course covering the basics of interior design principles, styles, and elements.\n   - **SketchUp for Interior Design**: Focuses on using SketchUp software to create 3D models of interior spaces.\n\n3. **Skillshare**:\n   - Various classes on topics ranging from color theory to space planning and decorating styles, often taught by experienced designers.\n\n4. **MasterClass**:\n   - **Kelly Wearstler Teaches Interior Design**: A well-known designer shares insights and techniques in a series of video lessons.\n\n5. **The Interior Design Institute**:\n   - Offers a comprehensive online diploma course that covers all aspects of interior design, from color theory to spatial planning.\n\n6. **New York School of Interior Design (NYSID)**:\n   - Offers a range of online courses including certificate and degree programs in interior design.\n\n7. **Interior Design Courses by Alison**:\n   - Free online courses on various aspects of interior design, including principles and practices.\n\n8. **FutureLearn**:\n   - Hosts courses from various universities and institutions, focusing on topics such as sustainable design and historical architecture.\n\n9. **Pluralsight**:\n   - Provides courses on specific software tools used in interior design, such as AutoCAD and SketchUp.\n\n10. **LinkedIn Learning**:\n    - Offers a variety of courses on interior design fundamentals, software training, and business skills for designers.\n\nWhen selecting a course, consider your specific interests, whether you want to focus on design theory, software skills, or practical applications. Also, read reviews and course descriptions to find the best fit for your goals.",
